North Korea absolutely refuses to unilateral disarmament without confidence
North Korea's foreign minister told the UN on Saturday that maintaining sanctions was escalating the country's mistrust of the US, which in such circumstances would absolutely refuse to give up its nuclear weapons unilaterally.
