Foreign buyers will be subject to higher stamp duty for the purchase of property in the UK
Foreign buyers will be subject to higher stamp duty for the purchase of property in the UK and additional cash flow will be used to help the homeless, according to Labour's new plans
The maneuver will neutralise the success of Corbyn's initiative to attract young voters
The increase in stamp duty will be applied to taxpayers who do not pay taxes in the UK
The Treasury plans to raise up to 120 million pounds a year to help the homeless
Foreign buyers will be subject to higher stamp duty to purchase property in the UK and the additional cash flow will be used to help the homeless, Theresa May will announce today.
The maneuver will be seen as an attempt to neutralize the success of Jeremy Corbyn's initiative to attract young voters with the promise of providing more affordable housing and higher incomes.
